1) Installing kafka
   a. Installing kafka using this page: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-apache-kafka-on-ubuntu-14-04
   b. Install java:
       i. sudo apt-get update
      ii. sudo apt-get install default-jre
   c. Install Zookeper:
       i. sudo apt-get install zookeeperd
      ii. Test it: Use 'telnet localhost 2181' and at prompt, send 'ruok'. It will respoind by: 'imok'

   b. These are the staps I followed on alpha42:
      i. useradd kafka -m
     ii. passwd kafka
    iii. adduser kafka sudo
     iv. su - kafka
      v. mkdir kafka  and then cd to it
     vi. wget http://apache.claz.org/kafka/1.0.0/kafka_2.11-1.0.0.tgz .
    vii. tar xvzf kafka_2.11-1.0.0.tgz. After untaring, move this dir to ~/kafka
   viii. Then: vi ~/kafka/config/server.properties and then add: "delete.topic.enable = true" to the end of the file
     ix. Now start kafka by: nohup ~/kafka/bin/kafka-server-start.sh ~/kafka/config/server.properties > ~/kafka/kafka.log 2>&1 &

   e. Now test the installation:
    i.   echo "Hello, World" | ~/kafka/bin/kafka-console-producer.sh --broker-list localhost:9092 --topic TutorialTopic > /dev/null
    ii. ~/kafka/bin/kafka-console-consumer.sh --zookeeper localhost:2181 --topic TutorialTopic --from-beginning

 
2) The first kafka on docker service was created by running the below:
   (this is from the article in: https://howtoprogram.xyz/2016/07/21/using-apache-kafka-docker/)
    docker run -d -p 2181:2181 --name zookeeper jplock/zookeeper
    docker run -d --name kafka1 --link zookeeper:zookeeper ches/kafka
    ZK_IP=$(docker inspect --format '{{ .NetworkSettings.IPAddress }}' zookeeper)
    KAFKA_IP=$(docker inspect --format '{{ .NetworkSettings.IPAddress }}' kafka1)
    echo $ZK_IP
    echo $KAFKA_IP
    docker run --rm ches/kafka kafka-topics.sh --create --topic test --replication-factor 1 --partitions 1 --zookeeper $ZK_IP:2181

3) Remote communications to this kafka was done using this article: https://aknay.github.io/2017/05/15/sending-messages-across-the-network-with-producer-and-consumer-using-kafka-and-zookeeper.html
    i) Changed kafka/config/server.properties:
           line: advertised.listeners=PLAINTEXT://alpha42.niaramfg.arubanetworks.com:9092

    ii)  

4) Kafka python was installed on all machines using either:
         1. pip install kafka-python
         2. conda install -c conda-forge kafka-python 


